{"type":"message","id":"418866cc","parentId":"e5992ca0","timestamp":"2026-02-12T19:01:59.469Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Analyzing Sleep Function**\n\nI'm focusing on the `sleep` function's behavior within the endurance test. It looks like a potential bottleneck. I've re-examined the code. I'm suspecting my calculations might be off. Specifically, `await sleep(batch.length * 10)` translates to 50ms for a batch. The `jitter` ranges from 800ms to 1200ms, which is roughly 1 second. I'm going to look at my implementation of the sleep function, and test again.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1770922918381_55","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"type endurance_test.js"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":""}],"api":"google-generative-ai","provider":"google","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":13832,"output":274,"cacheRead":12517,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14106,"cost":{"input":0.027663999999999998,"output":0.003288,"cacheRead":0.0025034000000000002,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.033455399999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1770922913412}}
{"type":"message","id":"092c0e1e","parentId":"418866cc","timestamp":"2026-02-12T19:02:00.361Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"exec_1770922918381_55","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"const fs = require('fs');\r\nconst path = require('path');\r\n\r\n// Configuration\r\nconst ITERATIONS = 100;\r\nconst TRADES_PER_BATCH = 5;\r\nconst TOTAL_TRADES = 500;\r\nconst JITTER_MIN = 800; // ms\r\nconst JITTER_MAX = 1200; // ms\r\nconst BALANCE_FILE = 'balance.json';\r\nconst TRADES_FILE = 'test_trades.json';\r\nconst REPORT_FILE = 'stress_test_report.md';\r\n\r\n// 1. Generate Test Data\r\nfunction generateTrades() {\r\n    const trades = [];\r\n    for (let i = 0; i < TOTAL_TRADES; i++) {\r\n        trades.push({\r\n            id: `trade_${i}`,\r\n            symbol: ['BTC', 'ETH', 'SOL', 'ADA'][Math.floor(Math.random() * 4)],\r\n            amount: (Math.random() * 10).toFixed(4),\r\n            price: (Math.random() * 50000).toFixed(2),\r\n            timestamp: Date.now()\r\n        });\r\n    }\r\n    fs.writeFileSync(TRADES_FILE, JSON.stringify(trades, null, 2));\r\n    console.log(`[SETUP] Generated ${TOTAL_TRADES} trades in ${TRADES_FILE}`);\r\n    return trades;\r\n}\r\n\r\n// Mock Balance File if not exists\r\nif (!fs.existsSync(BALANCE_FILE)) {\r\n    fs.writeFileSync(BALANCE_FILE, JSON.stringify({ balance: 10000, locked: false }, null, 2));\r\n}\r\n\r\n// Utilities\r\nconst sleep = (ms) => new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, ms));\r\n\r\nasync function simulateIteration(i, allTrades) {\r\n    const start = process.hrtime();\r\n    \r\n    // --- HYPE: Scan Item ---\r\n    // Simulation: fast operation\r\n    const scanTime = Math.random() * 50; // 0-50ms processing\r\n    await sleep(scanTime);\r\n\r\n    // --- NET: Jitter ---\r\n    const jitter = Math.floor(Math.random() * (JITTER_MAX - JITTER_MIN + 1) + JITTER_MIN);\r\n    await sleep(jitter);\r\n\r\n    // --- SENTINEL: Read Balance (Lock Check) ---\r\n    let lockStatus = 'OK';\r\n    try {\r\n        // Simulate potential contention by reading\r\n        const balanceData = fs.readFileSync(BALANCE_FILE, 'utf8');\r\n        JSON.parse(balanceData);\r\n    } catch (err) {\r\n        lockStatus = 'LOCKED';\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    // --- QUANT: Process Batch ---\r\n    const batchStart = (i - 1) * TRADES_PER_BATCH;\r\n    const batch = allTrades.slice(batchStart, batchStart + TRADES_PER_BATCH);\r\n    // Simulate processing time per trade\r\n    await sleep(batch.length * 10); \r\n\r\n    // --- LOG: Measure Time ---\r\n    const end = process.hrtime(start);\r\n    const durationMs = (end[0] * 1000 + end[1] / 1e6).toFixed(2);\r\n\r\n    return {\r\n        iteration: i,\r\n        durationMs: parseFloat(durationMs),\r\n        jitter,\r\n        lockStatus,\r\n        tradesProcessed: batch.length\r\n    };\r\n}\r\n\r\nasync function runTest() {\r\n    const trades = generateTrades();\r\n    const results = [];\r\n    \r\n    console.log(`[START] Starting 100 iterations...`);\r\n\r\n    for (let i = 1; i <= ITERATIONS; i++) {\r\n        const res = await simulateIteration(i, trades);\r\n        results.push(res);\r\n        if (i % 10 === 0) process.stdout.write('.');\r\n    }\r\n    console.log('\\n[DONE] Simulation complete.');\r\n\r\n    analyzeAndReport(results);\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction analyzeAndReport(results) {\r\n    // Analysis\r\n    const totalTime = results.reduce((acc, r) => acc + r.durationMs, 0);\r\n    const avgTime = totalTime / results.length;\r\n    const maxTime = Math.max(...results.map(r => r.durationMs));\r\n    const minTime = Math.min(...results.map(r => r.durationMs));\r\n    \r\n    // Drift Analysis (Split into first half vs second half)\r\n    const midPoint = Math.floor(results.length / 2);\r\n    const firstHalfAvg = results.slice(0, midPoint).reduce((acc, r) => acc + r.durationMs, 0) / midPoint;\r\n    const secondHalfAvg = results.slice(midPoint).reduce((acc, r) => acc + r.durationMs, 0) / (results.length - midPoint);\r\n    const drift = secondHalfAvg - firstHalfAvg;\r\n    \r\n    const lockFailures = results.filter(r => r.lockStatus !== 'OK').length;\r\n\r\n    // Token Estimation (Mock calculation)\r\n    // Assuming ~100 tokens input + ~50 tokens output per iteration logic if this were an LLM call\r\n    const estimatedTokensPerIter = 150; \r\n    const totalTokens24h = estimatedTokensPerIter * (24 * 60 * 60 / (avgTime / 1000)); // Extrapolated based on iteration speed\r\n\r\n    // Stability Status\r\n    let stability = \"STABLE\";\r\n    if (lockFailures > 0) stability = \"UNSTABLE (LOCKS)\";\r\n    if (drift > 200) stability = \"DEGRADING (LATENCY)\"; // Arbitrary threshold\r\n\r\n    // Generate Report\r\n    const reportContent = `\r\n# Stress Test Report: ENDURANCE-2026\r\n\r\n**[Agent] �?\" [100% Load] �?\" [${stability}]**\r\n\r\n## Executive Summary\r\n- **Iterations:** ${ITERATIONS}\r\n- **Total Duration:** ${(totalTime / 1000).toFixed(2)}s\r\n- **Average Latency:** ${avgTime.toFixed(2)}ms\r\n- **Latency Drift:** ${drift.toFixed(2)}ms (First Half: ${firstHalfAvg.toFixed(2)}ms vs Second Half: ${secondHalfAvg.toFixed(2)}ms)\r\n- **Lock Contention:** ${lockFailures} failures detected on ${BALANCE_FILE}\r\n\r\n## Analysis\r\n1. **Latency:** ${drift > 0 ? `Detected upward drift of ${drift.toFixed(2)}ms.` : `No significant latency drift detected.`}\r\n2. **File System:** ${lockFailures === 0 ? \"No file lock contention observed.\" : `WARNING: ${lockFailures} read collisions on balance file.`}\r\n3. **Resource Usage (Est):**\r\n   - Tokens per iteration: ~${estimatedTokensPerIter}\r\n   - Extrapolated 24h usage: ~${Math.round(totalTokens24h).toLocaleString()} tokens\r\n\r\n## Recommendation\r\n${drift > 500 ? \"Restart recommended every 4 hours due to significant latency leak.\" : \"System stable. Standard daily restart cycle (24h) is sufficient.\"}\r\n`;\r\n\r\n    fs.writeFileSync(REPORT_FILE, reportContent.trim());\r\n    console.log(`[REPORT] Written to ${REPORT_FILE}`);\r\n}\r\n\r\nrunTest();"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":890,"aggregated":"const fs = require('fs');\r\nconst path = require('path');\r\n\r\n// Configuration\r\nconst ITERATIONS = 100;\r\nconst TRADES_PER_BATCH = 5;\r\nconst TOTAL_TRADES = 500;\r\nconst JITTER_MIN = 800; // ms\r\nconst JITTER_MAX = 1200; // ms\r\nconst BALANCE_FILE = 'balance.json';\r\nconst TRADES_FILE = 'test_trades.json';\r\nconst REPORT_FILE = 'stress_test_report.md';\r\n\r\n// 1. Generate Test Data\r\nfunction generateTrades() {\r\n    const trades = [];\r\n    for (let i = 0; i < TOTAL_TRADES; i++) {\r\n        trades.push({\r\n            id: `trade_${i}`,\r\n            symbol: ['BTC', 'ETH', 'SOL', 'ADA'][Math.floor(Math.random() * 4)],\r\n            amount: (Math.random() * 10).toFixed(4),\r\n            price: (Math.random() * 50000).toFixed(2),\r\n            timestamp: Date.now()\r\n        });\r\n    }\r\n    fs.writeFileSync(TRADES_FILE, JSON.stringify(trades, null, 2));\r\n    console.log(`[SETUP] Generated ${TOTAL_TRADES} trades in ${TRADES_FILE}`);\r\n    return trades;\r\n}\r\n\r\n// Mock Balance File if not exists\r\nif (!fs.existsSync(BALANCE_FILE)) {\r\n    fs.writeFileSync(BALANCE_FILE, JSON.stringify({ balance: 10000, locked: false }, null, 2));\r\n}\r\n\r\n// Utilities\r\nconst sleep = (ms) => new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, ms));\r\n\r\nasync function simulateIteration(i, allTrades) {\r\n    const start = process.hrtime();\r\n    \r\n    // --- HYPE: Scan Item ---\r\n    // Simulation: fast operation\r\n    const scanTime = Math.random() * 50; // 0-50ms processing\r\n    await sleep(scanTime);\r\n\r\n    // --- NET: Jitter ---\r\n    const jitter = Math.floor(Math.random() * (JITTER_MAX - JITTER_MIN + 1) + JITTER_MIN);\r\n    await sleep(jitter);\r\n\r\n    // --- SENTINEL: Read Balance (Lock Check) ---\r\n    let lockStatus = 'OK';\r\n    try {\r\n        // Simulate potential contention by reading\r\n        const balanceData = fs.readFileSync(BALANCE_FILE, 'utf8');\r\n        JSON.parse(balanceData);\r\n    } catch (err) {\r\n        lockStatus = 'LOCKED';\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    // --- QUANT: Process Batch ---\r\n    const batchStart = (i - 1) * TRADES_PER_BATCH;\r\n    const batch = allTrades.slice(batchStart, batchStart + TRADES_PER_BATCH);\r\n    // Simulate processing time per trade\r\n    await sleep(batch.length * 10); \r\n\r\n    // --- LOG: Measure Time ---\r\n    const end = process.hrtime(start);\r\n    const durationMs = (end[0] * 1000 + end[1] / 1e6).toFixed(2);\r\n\r\n    return {\r\n        iteration: i,\r\n        durationMs: parseFloat(durationMs),\r\n        jitter,\r\n        lockStatus,\r\n        tradesProcessed: batch.length\r\n    };\r\n}\r\n\r\nasync function runTest() {\r\n    const trades = generateTrades();\r\n    const results = [];\r\n    \r\n    console.log(`[START] Starting 100 iterations...`);\r\n\r\n    for (let i = 1; i <= ITERATIONS; i++) {\r\n        const res = await simulateIteration(i, trades);\r\n        results.push(res);\r\n        if (i % 10 === 0) process.stdout.write('.');\r\n    }\r\n    console.log('\\n[DONE] Simulation complete.');\r\n\r\n    analyzeAndReport(results);\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction analyzeAndReport(results) {\r\n    // Analysis\r\n    const totalTime = results.reduce((acc, r) => acc + r.durationMs, 0);\r\n    const avgTime = totalTime / results.length;\r\n    const maxTime = Math.max(...results.map(r => r.durationMs));\r\n    const minTime = Math.min(...results.map(r => r.durationMs));\r\n    \r\n    // Drift Analysis (Split into first half vs second half)\r\n    const midPoint = Math.floor(results.length / 2);\r\n    const firstHalfAvg = results.slice(0, midPoint).reduce((acc, r) => acc + r.durationMs, 0) / midPoint;\r\n    const secondHalfAvg = results.slice(midPoint).reduce((acc, r) => acc + r.durationMs, 0) / (results.length - midPoint);\r\n    const drift = secondHalfAvg - firstHalfAvg;\r\n    \r\n    const lockFailures = results.filter(r => r.lockStatus !== 'OK').length;\r\n\r\n    // Token Estimation (Mock calculation)\r\n    // Assuming ~100 tokens input + ~50 tokens output per iteration logic if this were an LLM call\r\n    const estimatedTokensPerIter = 150; \r\n    const totalTokens24h = estimatedTokensPerIter * (24 * 60 * 60 / (avgTime / 1000)); // Extrapolated based on iteration speed\r\n\r\n    // Stability Status\r\n    let stability = \"STABLE\";\r\n    if (lockFailures > 0) stability = \"UNSTABLE (LOCKS)\";\r\n    if (drift > 200) stability = \"DEGRADING (LATENCY)\"; // Arbitrary threshold\r\n\r\n    // Generate Report\r\n    const reportContent = `\r\n# Stress Test Report: ENDURANCE-2026\r\n\r\n**[Agent] �?\" [100% Load] �?\" [${stability}]**\r\n\r\n## Executive Summary\r\n- **Iterations:** ${ITERATIONS}\r\n- **Total Duration:** ${(totalTime / 1000).toFixed(2)}s\r\n- **Average Latency:** ${avgTime.toFixed(2)}ms\r\n- **Latency Drift:** ${drift.toFixed(2)}ms (First Half: ${firstHalfAvg.toFixed(2)}ms vs Second Half: ${secondHalfAvg.toFixed(2)}ms)\r\n- **Lock Contention:** ${lockFailures} failures detected on ${BALANCE_FILE}\r\n\r\n## Analysis\r\n1. **Latency:** ${drift > 0 ? `Detected upward drift of ${drift.toFixed(2)}ms.` : `No significant latency drift detected.`}\r\n2. **File System:** ${lockFailures === 0 ? \"No file lock contention observed.\" : `WARNING: ${lockFailures} read collisions on balance file.`}\r\n3. **Resource Usage (Est):**\r\n   - Tokens per iteration: ~${estimatedTokensPerIter}\r\n   - Extrapolated 24h usage: ~${Math.round(totalTokens24h).toLocaleString()} tokens\r\n\r\n## Recommendation\r\n${drift > 500 ? \"Restart recommended every 4 hours due to significant latency leak.\" : \"System stable. Standard daily restart cycle (24h) is sufficient.\"}\r\n`;\r\n\r\n    fs.writeFileSync(REPORT_FILE, reportContent.trim());\r\n    console.log(`[REPORT] Written to ${REPORT_FILE}`);\r\n}\r\n\r\nrunTest();","cwd":"C:\\Users\\west2\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1770922920359}}
